{"build_type":"library","module_name":"link-name-returning-address","package_name":"link-name-returning-address","description":"Runtime name-to-address linker under launch: given a package name, ensure a code region (the shelf) exists on the calling thread, place the named object and its relocation closure on it, patch only the newly placed objects, and return the absolute entry address (region base plus the name's placed offset). Establishes a fresh per-thread shelf on first use (loader globals are per-thread, so a worker thread starts with none) exactly as the legacy loader did, then reuses it for later names. Idempotent: a name already on the shelf returns its address without reloading. Reads bytes through the existing by-name import using the loader libdir set by the caller. Callers hand the returned address to the launch tail-chain or invoke it directly.","function_definitions":{"link-name-returning-address":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"name","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"map_len","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":268435456},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"prot_rwx","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":7},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"map_flags","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":34},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"map_fd","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":-1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"e_notfound","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"linked_name_absent_from_map"},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"region","nam